content:
The chunk describes the definition of texture files and material attributes in Panda's file format, including scalar values for diffuse, ambient, emissive, and specular properties. This information is situated within a comprehensive document explaining various aspects of defining 3D models and animations in Panda, including groups, joints, bundles, tables, and vertex pools.

Context: The chunk defines texture and material attributes in Panda's file format, following the explanation of vertex pools, to describe how geometry can be shaded and textured.

Textures

This describes a texture file that can be referenced later with <TRef> { name }:

<Texture> name {
  filename
  <Scalar> scalar1 { value1 }
  <Scalar> scalar2 { value2 }
}

Texture Scalars

The following attributes are presently implemented for textures:

Materials

This defines a set of material attributes that may later be referenced with <MRef> { name }:

<Material> name {
  [scalars]
}

Material Scalars

<Scalar> diffr { number }
<Scalar> diffg { number }
<Scalar> diffb { number }
<Scalar> diffa { number }
<Scalar> ambr { number }
<Scalar> ambg { number }
<Scalar> ambb { number }
<Scalar> amba { number }
<Scalar> emitr { number }
